OL,6,FThe survey included the option for
OL,7,Fdoctors to record experiences of where
OL,8,Fthey work ` with more than 575 sharing
OL,9,Ftheir concerns, with a major focus on
OL,10,Fthe impact on patients.
OL,12,FOne testimony reads: "It has become
OL,13,Fthe norm to be operating at 115-120%
OL,14,Fcapacity and have between 10 and 20
OL,15,Fadmissions sleeping in the ED
OL,16,Fovernight in corridors.
OL,18,F"The system is broken and needs to be
OL,19,Faddressed as an emergency."
